3 SECTION 2. AMENDMENT. Section 62.1-02-05 of the North Dakota Century Code is
4 amended and reenacted as follows:
5 62.1-02-05. Possession of a firearm or dangerous weapon at a public gathering -
6 Penalty - Application.
7 1. An individual may not possess a firearm or dangerous weapon at:
8 a. A school or school-sponsored event on school property;
9 b. A church or other place of worship; or
10 c. A publicly owned or operated building.
11 2. This section does not apply to:
12 a. A law enforcement officer, or a correctional officer employed by the department of
13 corrections and rehabilitation or by a correctional facility governed by chapter
14 12-44.1. A correctional officer employed by the department of corrections and
15 rehabilitation may carry a firearm only as authorized in section 12-47-34. A
16 correctional officer employed by a correctional facility governed by chapter
17 12-44.1 may carry a firearm or dangerous weapon only as authorized in section
18 12-44.1-30;
19 b. An individual who is on an ambulance or firefighter crew while the individual is on
20 duty if:
21 (1) The individual has written permission from the governing body or owner of
22 the fire department or ambulance service;
23 (2) The individual possesses a valid class 1 concealed weapons license;
24 (3) The individual has successfully completed a weapons training course
25 developed by the North Dakota private investigative and security board; and
26 (4) The governing body or owner of the fire department or ambulance crew
27 provides written notice to the bureau of criminal investigation of the
28 individuals authorized or no longer authorized to carry a firearm or
29 dangerous weapon under this section, including that all training and
30 certification requirements have been satisfied;
